		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I will not pretend to know anything about patents, because I don't. But if the Gameboy and the Master System both have built in scanline counters (do they? I'm not 100% sure, but I think they do), and they were made by different companies, there must have been a way. If the Gameboy was made by Nintendo, there should have been a way for the NES to have one too.
<br />
<br />Anyway, nothing can be done about that now. I still like to develop for the NES even if coding raster effects for it is kind of a pain! =)

		

